pageContext.claim: “They wanted it so badly -- San Diego.  They wanted it so badly.  And I said, you know, if we build it, we will lose a big constituency, because there won't be anybody saying, "We want the wall."  But we had to build it.  So I know they're very happy about it.”
pageContext.analysis: San Diego does not support construction of the wall; even the Republican mayor is opposed. The wall is not being constructed in San Diego; Trump has been unable to win funding from Congress.
